%20Telegram.%20Units%20receiving%20drones%20from%20Sternenko%20post%20videos%20of%20battlefield%20hits%2C%20mixing%20heavy%20metal%20soundtrack%20with%20footage%20of%20their%20drones%20blasting%20into%20infantry%20troops%20and%20artillery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225023%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Activist%20Serhii%20Sternenko%20during%20interview%20to%20Ukrainian%20media%20in%20November.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a83d6ba17a8c5b40534abc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223349%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESternenko%2C%20trained%20as%20a%20lawyer%2C%20is%20a%20prominent%20internet%20personality%20in%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ilia%2C%20the%20crowdfunding%20movement%20is%20turning%20his%20pocket%20change%20into%20real%20combat%20power%20that%20he%20can%20witness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20remarkably%20cost-effective%20formula%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-us-must-prepare-for-next-war-american-veteran-ukraine-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage%20of%20modern%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Sternenko%20Foundation%20typically%20aims%20to%20raise%20%24250%2C000%20per%20day%2C%20and%20its%20recipients%20say%20they%20are%20inflicting%20damage%20to%20Russian%20military%20hardware%20that%20collectively%20reaches%20into%20the%20billions%20of%20dollars%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20As%20is%20the%20norm%2C%20they%20back%20up%20most%20hits%20with%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20famed%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20fund%2C%20the%20Ronin%20drone%20unit%20of%20the%2065th%20Separate%20Mechanized%20Brigade%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20touts%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20war's%20most%20audacious%20examples%20of%20asymmetric%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERonin%20pilots%20said%20in%20January%20that%20they%20had%20used%20a%2010-inch%20FPV%20drone%2C%20worth%20%24500%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-ronin-drones-civilian-funded-russian-air-defense-destroyed-day-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisable%20a%20Buk%3C%2Fa%3E%20medium-range%20air%20defense%20system%20estimated%20to%20be%20worth%20about%20%2440%20million.%20An%20uploaded%20video%20showed%20a%20drone%20approaching%20a%20modern%20Buk-M3%20launcher%20from%20on%20high%2C%20before%20slamming%20into%20its%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelegram.org%2Fjs%2Ftelegram-widget.js%3F22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20Ronin%20FPV%20drones%20pushed%20deeper%20and%20deeper%20into%20Russian-held%20territory.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20pilots%20uploaded%20videos%20of%20attacks%20against%20six%20more%20Buk%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20Ronin%20pilots%20said%20they%20had%20struck%20just%20one%20of%20the%20SAMs.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20summer%20in%202025%2C%20their%20videos%20showed%20that%20they'd%20hit%20at%20least%2015%20in%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff028e0d-a0a1-43e2-9599-7282e7c42182%5C%22%3EThe%20wrath%20of%20donated%20drones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20Buk%20strikes%20only%20happened%20because%20of%20Sternenko's%20drones%2C%20a%20pilot%20from%20the%20Ronin%20unit%2C%20named%20Andriy%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sternenko%20Foundation%20says%20it's%20delivered%20over%20210%2C000%20drones%20since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-can-jam-own-drones-many-some-russian-share-signals-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.2%20million%20total%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Ukraine%20reported%20producing%20in%202024%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPilots%20like%20Andriy%2C%20however%2C%20say%20Sternenko's%20drones%20are%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBattlefield%20conditions%20shift%20fast%2C%20so%20the%20Sternenko%20team%20regularly%20asks%20pilots%20what%20upgrades%20are%20needed.%20Andriy%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-dronemakers-war-unwinnable-dirt-cheap-crowdfunding-veterans-civilians-russia-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evolunteers%20swiftly%20relay%20that%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20manufacturers%2C%20and%20then%20deliver%20drones%20with%20updated%20hardware%20and%20software%20in%20days%20or%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20at%20night%2C%20if%20we%20are%20on%20the%20attack%2C%20and%20any%20problems%20arise%2C%20we%20are%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20drone%20developer%2C%20and%20we%20can%20solve%20it%20on%20the%20spot%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senior%20soldier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20short%20feedback%20loop%20allowed%20for%20constant%20small%20tweaks%20to%20Sternenko's%20drones%2C%20Andriy%20said%2C%20so%20the%20Ronin%20pilots%20gradually%20improved%20their%2010-inch%20platforms.%20These%20are%20the%20workhorses%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-drone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine's%20FPV%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20radio-controlled%2C%20battery-powered%20quadcopters%20that%20use%207-%20to%2012-inch%20propellers%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%20designed%20as%20flying%20cameras%2C%20they've%20become%20one%20of%20the%20war's%20primary%20weapons%20after%20soldiers%20started%20fitting%20the%20cheap%20platforms%20with%20small%2C%20explosive%20payloads%20like%20rocket-propelled%20grenades%20that%20typically%20weigh%2010%20pounds%20or%20less.%20Pilots%20fly%20them%20right%20into%20their%20targets%20%E2%80%94%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20fortified%20positions%2C%20and%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%20are%20now%20locked%20in%20a%20perpetual%20race%20to%20develop%20new%20drone%20defenses%2C%20such%20as%20jammers%20that%20disrupt%20their%20radio%20signals%2C%20which%20drives%20the%20need%20for%20constant%20upgrades%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20man%20holds%20an%20FPV%20quadcopter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68abfdc1a17a8c5b40536341%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20volunteer%20holds%20a%20ready-made%20FPV%20drone%20in%20a%20drone%20workshop%20in%20April%202024%20in%20Lviv.%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20updates%20on%20Sternenko's%20funded%20drones%2C%20the%20Ronins%20eventually%20received%20FPV%20quadcopters%20that%20could%20fly%20reliably%20beyond%2018%20miles.%20Many%20of%20Russia's%20Buks%20were%20positioned%20beyond%20that%20limit%2C%20Andriy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20hitting%20Buks%20as%20fast%20and%20as%20efficiently%20as%20we%20could%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20drone%20pilot%20said.%20Sternenko's%20volunteers%20also%20provided%20a%20new%20type%20of%20drone%20that%20acted%20as%20a%20signal%20repeater%2C%20he%20said%2C%20strengthening%20the%20wireless%20communications%20link%20between%20the%20drone%20and%20its%20operator%20in%20jammed%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndriy%20said%20the%20Ronin%20unit%20typically%20takes%20three%20to%20four%20FPV%20drones%20to%20finish%20off%20a%20Buk%20air%20defense%20system%20and%20estimates%20that%20it%20cost%20them%2055%20drones%2C%20or%20%2427%2C500%2C%20to%20disable%2015%20systems%20collectively%20worth%20between%20%24150%20million%20and%20%24600%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b4b4e8b-fdf0-487f-b8df-66c224359c26%5C%22%3EA%20striking%20cost%20ratio%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20cost%20ratio%20means%20that%20for%20every%20%241%20spent%20by%20donors%20through%20Sternenko%2C%20the%20Ronin%20pilots%20were%20inflicting%20at%20least%20roughly%20%245%2C450%20worth%20of%20damage%20to%20Russia's%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndependent%20analysts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it's%20difficult%20to%20determine%20the%20exact%20dollar%20value%20of%20these%20strikes%2C%20but%20that%20their%20cost%20efficiency%20is%20astronomically%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20Buk-M3%20battery%20is%20valued%20at%20around%20%24100%20million%2C%20but%20that%20would%20be%20the%20export%20price%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Benjamin%20Blandin%2C%20a%20researcher%20with%20the%20Japanese%20nonprofit%20Yokosuka%20Council%20on%20Asia-Pacific%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20batteries%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-us-mixing-unusual-weapons-together-for-improved-defense-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuch%20as%20the%20Buk-M1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20might%20have%20cost%20foreign%20customers%20around%20%2445%20million.%20Still%2C%20Blandin%20cautioned%20that%20the%20Russian%20defense%20ministry%20is%20known%20to%20purchase%20homegrown%20assets%2C%20such%20as%20tanks%20like%20the%20T-72%2C%20at%20a%20far%20cheaper%20rate%20than%20the%20sale%20price%20for%20other%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20estimates%20say%20that%2C%20with%20such%20a%20deep%20discount%2C%20the%20Buk-M1%20costs%20Moscow%20about%20%2410%20million%20per%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224824%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20Buk-M2%20missile%20launcher%20drives%20at%20the%20Red%20Square%20in%20Moscow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68abfecdcfc04e97619bee44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223054%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Buk%20relies%20on%20launchers%20and%20radars%20that%20work%20in%20tandem%20to%20counter%20air%20threats.%3Cp%3EAlexander%20NEMENOV%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Buk%20battery%20also%20consists%20of%20many%20parts%2C%20including%20multiple%20launchers%2C%20a%20command%20post%2C%20and%20a%20main%20radar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%2C%20the%20radar%20itself%2C%20and%20fire%20control%20computers%20are%20the%20most%20expensive%20part%20of%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Tollast%2C%20a%20researcher%20of%20land%20warfare%20for%20the%20UK-based%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20analyzing%20the%20Ronin%20videos%20of%20Buk%20hits%2C%20he%20said%20the%20unit%20clearly%20damaged%20radars%20in%20some%20clips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiemon%20Wezeman%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20of%20arms%20transfers%20for%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%2C%20said%20that%20destroying%20one%20critical%20Buk%20component%2C%20such%20as%20the%20main%20radar%2C%20could%20put%20the%20rest%20out%20of%20action%2C%20prompting%20Ukrainians%20to%20say%20they%20destroyed%20the%20entire%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20no%20matter%20what%20price%20is%20taken%20or%20how%20out-of-action%20the%20system%20had%20been%20made%2C%20it's%20still%20a%20very%20much%20higher%20USD%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Evalue%20lost%20than%20that%20of%20a%20few%20drones%20used%20against%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20US%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221106d741-d9d5-4f79-b054-76e17def2778%5C%22%3EDonated%20drones%2C%20a%20class%20above%20the%20rest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20realizing%20its%20Buks%20were%20being%20hunted%2C%20started%20pulling%20them%20further%20away%20from%20the%20frontline%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20Andriy%20said.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%20his%20unit%20was%20able%20to%20use%20donated%20drones%20to%20hit%20a%20Buk%20at%20a%20distance%20of%2055%20kilometers%2C%20or%2034%20miles%20%E2%80%94%20a%20staggering%20feat%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-defense-tech-industry-warfare-russia-attacks-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoday's%20FPV%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20mentioned%20the%20distance%20to%20other%20foundations%2C%20their%20eyes%20went%20wide%20with%20surprise%2C%26quot%3B%20Andriy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20roughly%2030%20to%2040%20FPV%20drones%20he%20pilots%20in%20a%20two-day%20shift%2C%20Andriy%20estimated%20that%2095%25%20typically%20come%20from%20the%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225668%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%20holds%20a%20controller%20with%20his%20thumbs%20and%20forefinger%20on%20both%20control%20sticks%20and%20his%20middle%20fingers%20on%20the%20edges%20of%20the%20controller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68abff52194a2d49b8af1582%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20drone%20pilots%20receiving%20drones%20from%20Sternenko%20said%20they%20greatly%20prefer%20volunteer%20FPVs.%3Cp%3EMaks%20Muravsky%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20also%20receive%20drones%20purchased%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense.%20Andriy%20said%20these%20can%20be%20outdated%2C%20and%20he%20prefers%20the%20crowdfunded%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commander%20of%20the%20Dovbush%20Hornets%2C%20the%20drone%20unit%20of%20the%2068th%20Jaeger%20Brigade%20in%20Pokrovsk%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20state-funded%20drone%20deliveries%20suffer%20from%20a%20typical%20issue%20that%20plagues%20governments%3A%20It%20can%20take%20too%20long%20to%20turn%20immediate%20feedback%20into%20updated%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20war%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-company-makes-new-fiber-optic-drone-100-kilometer-reach-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechniques%20and%20jamming%20frequencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20evolve%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20weeks%2C%20that%20delay%20can%20be%20the%20difference%20between%20victory%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20Sternenko%20situation%2C%20their%20representatives%20call%20the%20unit%20and%20ask%20what%20specific%20technical%20characteristics%20of%20drones%20they%20need%2C%20and%20they%20just%20buy%20the%20one%20that%20suits%20the%20unit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20major%2C%20whose%20call%20sign%20is%20Fierce.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20they%20already%20have%20the%20drones%20accumulated%2C%20so%20they%20just%20give%20them%20to%20the%20unit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState-funded%20drones%20are%20needed%2C%20but%20often%20have%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20manufacturer%20for%20retweaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20work%20on%20FPV%20drones%20together%20in%20a%20workshop.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68ac002fa17a8c5b40536345%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20Ukraine%20is%20filled%20with%20drone%20manufacturers%2C%20some%20military%20units%20also%20have%20their%20own%20drone%20workshops%20and%20specialists.%3Cp%3EScott%20Peterson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20drones%20are%20sometimes%20impossible%20to%20use%20on%20certain%20sections%20of%20the%20front%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20Fierce%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20fighters%20have%20to%20invest%20their%20own%20salaries%20in%20the%20drones%2C%20to%20modify%20them%20and%20change%20the%20control%20frequencies.%20It%20takes%20time%20and%20their%20personal%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20was%20common%20enough%20for%20the%20Sternenko%20Foundation%20to%20launch%20a%20refitting%20project%20for%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20drones%2C%20called%20reDrone%2C%20primarily%20to%20add%20hardware%20upgrades%20such%20as%20motor%20controllers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Ukraine's%20Defense%20Ministry%20said%20that%20its%20provided%20FPV%20drones%20are%20purchased%20from%20private%20manufacturers%20%26quot%3Bto%20create%20a%20sustainable%2C%20large-scale%2C%20and%20predictable%20supply%20system%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20wartime%20conditions%2C%20certain%20units%20may%20have%20specific%20needs%20that%20can%20be%20promptly%20met%20through%20volunteer%20initiatives%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20flexibility%20of%20drone%20supplies%20from%20volunteers%20complements%20the%20large-scale%20state%20system%20of%20equipping%20the%20army.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af26628a-ab90-4b64-b319-e7850ee72ea5%5C%22%3ECivilians%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20fight%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Konotop%2C%20just%2060%20miles%20from%20the%20northern%20front%2C%20Ilia%20is%20also%20a%20volunteer.%20He%20said%20he's%20driven%20donated%20vehicles%20and%20equipment%20dozens%20of%20times%20to%20soldiers%20in%20the%20greater%20Sumy%20and%20wartorn%20Donbas%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIlia%20said%20he%20was%20nearly%20killed%20on%20four%20occasions%20on%20these%20supply%20runs%20near%20the%20frontlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGod%20decided%20I%20am%20more%20useful%20here%20on%20this%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20laughed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-defense-industry-changing-how-west-thinks-about-war-russia-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estrained%20from%20years%20of%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20long%20relied%20on%20its%20civilians%20to%20support%20the%20front%20with%20battle%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20war%20is%20a%20black%20hole%20that%20just%20keeps%20sucking%20up%20all%20of%20our%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Oleksandr%20Skarlat%2C%20the%20Sternenko%20Foundation's%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20donations%20received%20by%20the%20foundation%20come%20in%20small%20amounts%20from%20Ukrainian%20civilians%2C%20said%20Skarlat%2C%20a%20national%20finswimming%20athlete%20before%20the%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20foundation%20says%20it%20raises%20roughly%20300%20million%20hryvnia%2C%20or%20about%20%247.2%20million%2C%20from%20over%20450%2C000%20individual%20contributions%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20operates%20like%20a%20hub%2C%20connecting%20manufacturers%20with%20drone%20units%2C%20then%20paying%20for%20and%20delivering%20drones%20to%20those%20troops%2C%20Skarlat%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20foundation's%20advantage%20is%20speed%20and%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAn%20expensive%20drone%20is%20not%20always%20better.%20If%20new%20components%20are%20released%2C%20they%20must%20be%20purchased%20and%20transferred%20to%20the%20units%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221783%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Soldiers%20with%20blurred%20faces%20hold%20up%20FPV%20drones%20received%20from%20Sternenko's%20foundation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a83521a17a8c5b40534aaa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22954%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20a%20drone%20unit%20record%20themselves%20thanking%20the%20Sternenko%20Foundation%20for%20a%20new%20delivery%20of%20FPV%20drones%20on%20August%2020.%3Cp%3ESternenko%20Foundation%20website%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20process%20is%20now%20a%20well-oiled%20machine%2C%20but%20it%20is%20limited%20by%20whatever%20resources%20Sternenko's%20team%20can%20raise.%20They%20try%20to%20prioritize%20squads%20that%20produce%20better%20results%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Ronins%20and%20Dovbush%20Hornets%2C%20which%20operate%20in%20Pokrovsk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESternenko%2C%20a%20popular%20internet%20personality%2C%20uses%20his%20following%20to%20promote%20fundraisers%20and%20repost%20strike%20footage%20uploaded%20by%20recipient%20units.%20In%20May%2C%20he%20was%20shot%20in%20the%20t