ure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mom%20and%20daughter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b71a91a17a8c5b4053dcd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20mom%20cooks%20dinner%20for%20the%20family%20every%20Sunday%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20reason%20we%20moved%20into%20the%20same%20house%20was%20to%20be%20able%20to%20help%20her.%20Despite%20a%20few%20medical%20scares%2C%20she%20helped%20us%20as%20well.%20The%20kids%20visit%20and%20work%20on%20puzzles%20or%20games%20in%20Granny's%20living%20room.%20She%20spends%20hours%20going%20over%20letter%20sounds%20and%20reading%20books%20with%20the%20younger%20kids.%20With%20endless%20driving%20needs%20to%20get%20the%20kids%20to%20ballet%20or%20school%2C%20she%20joined%20the%20constant%20juggle%20of%20how%20to%20get%20each%20kid%20to%20the%20right%20destination.%20She%20continues%20to%20cook%20Sunday%20night%20dinner%20for%20all%2013%20of%20us%20every%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20didn't%20grow%20up%20near%20my%20relatives.%20My%20adopted%20parents'%20families%20lived%20in%20England%20and%20Scotland.%20I%20only%20saw%20them%20a%20few%20times%20throughout%20my%20childhood.%20My%20husband's%20grandparents%20lived%20five%20hours%20away%20from%20him.%20He%20spent%20every%20holiday%20with%20them%2C%20and%20they%20attended%20all%20the%20important%20milestones%2C%20but%20he%20wished%20they%20were%20closer.%20I'm%20so%20grateful%20that%20Mom%20wanted%20to%20give%20multigenerational%20living%20a%20try.%20Now%2C%20she's%20only%20a%20few%20steps%20away.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-mom-lives-with-me-and-my-ten-kids-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757256121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F